For improved performance when hashing large strings, consider using `withUTF8` to get a buffer pointer to the string's UTF-8 bytes and passing that to the hasher. This avoids allocating an intermediate `Array` and is more idiomatic for hashing raw byte contents.

```swift
  public func hash(into hasher: inout Hasher) {
    hasher.combine(domainRank)
    payload.withUTF8 { buffer in
      hasher.combine(bytes: UnsafeRawBufferPointer(buffer))
    }
  }

```

